# Peanut Butter Cupcakes

Based on [https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/peanut-butter-cupcakes](https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/peanut-butter-cupcakes)

{ rating=0 image="None" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

### Cupcakes

- [ ] 1.25 cups all-purpose flour, spooned & leveled
- [ ] 1/2 tsp baking soda
- [ ] 1/4 tsp salt
- [ ] 1/2 cup canola or vegetable oil
- [ ] 1/2 cup creamy peanut butter
- [ ] 1 cup packed light or dark brown sugar
- [ ] 1 large egg, at room temperature
- [ ] 1/3 cup sour cream, at room temperature
- [ ] 1.5 tsp pure vanilla extract
- [ ] 3/4 cup whole milk, at room temperature
- [ ] 1/3 cup very finely crushed or chopped peanuts

### Chocolate Peanut Butter Frosting

- [ ] 1 cup (16 Tbsps) unsalted butter, softened
- [ ] 3.5 cups confectioners' sugar
- [ ] 1/2 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
- [ ] 3 Tbsps heavy cream or milk
- [ ] 1/3 cup creamy peanut butter
- [ ] 1 tsp pure vanilla extract
- [ ] 1/4 tsp salt
- [ ] Optional: mini Reese's Peanut Butter Cups or chopped peanuts for garnish

## Recipe

1. Preheat oven to 350°F (177°C). Line a 12-cup muffin pan with cupcake liners. Add 2-3 liners to a second pan since this recipe yields 14-15 cupcakes.
1. Whisk together flour, baking soda, and salt in a medium bowl; set aside.
1. Using a handheld or stand mixer, combine oil, peanut butter, brown sugar, egg, sour cream, and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, milk, and peanuts; mix until combined without overmixing.
1. Fill liners two-thirds full. Bake 21-23 minutes until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean and tops spring back when touched. (Mini cupcakes: bake 11-13 minutes.) Cool completely before frosting.
1. Beat softened butter on medium speed until creamy, about 2 minutes.
1. Add confectioners' sugar, cocoa powder, and milk; beat on low for 30 seconds.
1. Add peanut butter, vanilla, and salt; beat on medium-high for 2 minutes until combined.
1. Adjust consistency with more confectioners' sugar if too thin or cream/milk if too thick.
1. Frost cooled cupcakes and garnish with peanut butter cups or chopped peanuts if desired.

## Notes

- Store leftovers covered in the refrigerator for up to 5 days
- A cupcake carrier is recommended for storing and transporting decorated cupcakes
